      "description": "A parametric CFD sweep across ±15% impeller clearance and ±10% volute width variations was conducted to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. Predicted hemolysis indices across the design space were assessed for monotonicity and convergence. The sweep confirms that nominal geometry represents a local minimum in hemolysis response; worst-case geometry deviations remain below the RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to the predicate device. Validation activities were conducted at conditions representative of intraoperative CPB flow demands. Assurance level for this result is assessed as High based on mesh independence confirmation and turbulence model sensitivity study; structured comparator reference is subsumed within the narrative above rather than enumerated as a discrete dataset binding.",
